[3] Nigeria: wife of Ebola survivor delivers baby girl
Date: Fri 4 Dec 2015
Source: AllAfrica, This Day report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201512040269.html


Nigeria: wife of Ebola survivor delivers baby girl in First Consultants Hospital
A healthy baby girl was born to [Dr Ada Igonoh] who is an Ebola virus disease (EVD) survivor. [Dr Igonoh] delivered the baby on 1 Dec 2015. According to the medical director of the hospital, Dr Benjamin Ohiaeri, "The baby girl, weighing 3 kg [6.6 lb] at birth (its placenta 450 g [1 lb]), a product of a term gestation, was delivered following strict guidelines and recommendations from the Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), USA, through the pre-natal and delivery stages." -- more

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Media reports fail to note the important point that since Nigeria was declared Ebola-free on 19 Oct 2014 http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/137091/1/roadmapsitrep22Oct2014_eng.pdf, this lucky baby was conceived long after her father recovered from Ebola, showing that not all male survivors transmit infection sexually.

See also: 3 Nov 2015 Nigeria: Ebola survivor, Dr Ada Igonoh delivered of a baby girl
http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/11/nig-ebola-survivor-dr-ada-igonoh-delivered-of-a-baby-girl. - Mod.JW]

